*linbox-1.4.0 (26 Feb 2016)

  26 Feb 2016; François Bissey <francois.bissey@canterbury.ac.nz>
  +linbox-1.4.0.ebuild, linbox-1.3.2-r2.ebuild:
  sci-libs/linbox: new linbox, work in progress upstream.

  25 Feb 2016; François Bissey <francois.bissey@canterbury.ac.nz>
  linbox-1.3.2-r2.ebuild:
  sci-libs/linbox: be a bit more precise with the givaro dependency

  31 Jan 2016; François Bissey <francois.bissey@canterbury.ac.nz> metadata.xml:
  sci-libs/linbox: update metadata

  23 Jan 2016; François Bissey <francois.bissey@canterbury.ac.nz>
  files/linbox-1.3.2-clang-fix.patch, linbox-1.3.2-r2.ebuild:
  sci-libs/linbox: move to EAPI 6, make repoman happy

  14 Oct 2015; François Bissey <francois.bissey@canterbury.ac.nz>
  linbox-1.3.2-r2.ebuild:
  sci-libs/linbox: added subslot dependency on ntl

  07 Sep 2015; François Bissey <francois.bissey@canterbury.ac.nz>
  linbox-1.3.2-r2.ebuild:
  Massive ebuild format clean up. One removal. Further QA to follow.

*linbox-1.3.2-r2 (25 Jun 2015)

  25 Jun 2015; François Bissey <francois.bissey@canterbury.ac.nz>
  +linbox-1.3.2-r2.ebuild, -files/linbox-1.3.2-lapack_detection.patch,
  -linbox-1.3.2-r1.ebuild, -linbox-1.3.2.ebuild:
  Leveraging the latest change in fflas-ffpack to deal with lapack. Remove fix
  to lapack detection in configure, the configure test is  actually not used to
  determine the availability of lapack, the content of fflas-ffpack-config.h is.

